race.comment: DREAM LANTERN (11) jumped awkwardly and had the job ahead from that point onwards last time out when favourite in a Class 4 over this trip at Ipswich. Very fit mare who is well in after the claim. Just needs luck from a horror draw to be highly competitive. Consistent mare SIRKEL (13) came with a well-time run to score in a similar race to this at Eagle Farm recently. Loves racing here so although getting up in the weights she is a winning hope again. ESTRONDO (2) has plenty of weight but he has won two from two here at 1200m so his credentials are hard to fault. STREAK OF WINNING (6) returned with a bang at Toowoomba when living right up to his market support. This is obviously tougher but he has more to offer and is worth including.
